import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='X', y='Y')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', kde=True, color='blue', label='X Distribution')
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['X'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', kde=True, color='blue', label='Y Distribution')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='X', data=data, label='X', color='blue')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='Y', data=data, label='Y', color='green')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.legend(title='Variables', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='group', y='value', hue='variable', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y for different groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Variable', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
